SPEAKER of the Kogi State House of Assembly, Rt Hon Prince Matthew Kolawole has and congratulated, Dr Mrs Folashade Yemi-Esan, the newly appointed acting Head of Service of the Federation. In a press statement issued on Friday by Femi Olugbemi, Chief Press Secretary to the Speaker, the Speaker rejoiced with the people and Government of Kogi State and appreciates President Muhammad Buhari for finding one of us worthy to be giving such assignment at this critical time in our country where the next level team led by President Muhammadu Buhari is in haste to move the nation to another level of development. ALSO READ: https://tribuneonlineng.com/obono-obla-oyo-ita-corruption-allegations-buharis-presidency-stinks-pdp/ Oyetola mourns Osun Customary Court President 44-year-old driver kills three in-laws in Edo Budget, security our major priority ― Senate President UPDATE: Atiku Abubakar writes Nigerians, solicits for more… He said her appointment at this time is well thought out considering her wealth of experience as an outstanding administrator who has spent major parts of life in the public service. Rt Hon Kolawole said the new Head of Service is a career civil servant that is known for her probity, work ethic and robust experience in the civil service, little wonder her spotless resume qualified her to be appointed by President Muhammadu Buhari. He said the Ijumu born Mrs Yemi Esan as a former Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Petroleum Resources has all it takes to succeed in her new office, urging her not to betray the confidence reposed in her. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
